luent, light weight music player written in GTK4.</li>","updatedAt":"2022-08-09T20:41:09.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Apps</h2><h3>Virtualization</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://gitlab.gnome.org/GNOME/gnome-boxes\">GNOME Boxes</a> - A simple GNOME 3 application to access virtual machines.</li>","updatedAt":"2022-08-09T20:41:09.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Editor Plugins</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/technosophos/Vala-TMBundle\">Vala-TMBundle</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/technosophos/Vala-TMBundle\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">21</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":21,\"repo\":\"technosophos/Vala-TMBundle\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - A TextMate bundle that provides Vala syntax highlighting, code completion, etc. Sublime Text 3 can also use this plugin.</li>","updatedAt":"2022-08-09T20:41:09.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Editor Plugins</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://atom.io/packages/language-vala-modern\">language-vala-modern</a> - Provides Vala language support in Atom. It's a fork of the unmaintained \"language-vala package\".</li>","updatedAt":"2022-08-09T20:41:09.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Editor Plugins</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://launchpad.net/valasyntax4sublimetext\">Vala Syntax 4 Sublime Text</a> - A basic plugin for Sublime Text 3 that provides syntax highlighting.</li>","updatedAt":"2022-08-09T20:41:09.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Libraries</h2><h3>Graphics Libraries</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://gegl.org/babl/\">Babl</a> - A dynamic, any to any, pixel format translation library.</li>","updatedAt":"2022-08-09T20:41:09.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Libraries</h2><h3>Graphics Libraries</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/ev3dev/grx\">GRX</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/ev3dev/grx\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">13</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":13,\"repo\":\"ev3dev/grx\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - A graphics library for simple graphics displays (think 1-bit displays or Adafruit's PiTFT displays). It also includes keyboard, mouse, joystick and touchscreen input support.</li>","updatedAt":"2022-08-09T20:41:09.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Libraries</h2><h3>Graphics Libraries</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.libsdl.org/\">SDL2</a> - A cross-platform development library designed to provide low level access to audio, keyboard, mouse, joystick, and graphics hardware via OpenGL, Direct3D, and Vulkan. Bindings are included in Vala and will be available starting with Vala 0.52.</li>","updatedAt":"2022-08-09T20:41:09.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Libraries</h2><h3>Web Development</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/valum-framework/valum\">Valum</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/valum-framework/valum\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">213</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":213,\"repo\":\"valum-framework/valum\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - A Web micro-framework entirely written in Vala.</li>","updatedAt":"2022-08-09T20:41:09.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Apps</h2><h3>Cryptography &#x26; Security</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://gitlab.com/vinarisoftware/integrity-check-gtk\">Integrity Check</a> -  Linux application written in Vala and GTK, designed to get the verification sum of a file (MD5, SHA1, SHA256) and compare to the sum of verification provided by the file creator.</li>","updatedAt":"2022-08-09T20:34:59.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Apps</h2><h3>Productivity</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://gitlab.gnome.org/GNOME/gnome-calculator\">GNOME Calculator</a> - The calculator app for the GNOME desktop.</li>","updatedAt":"2022-07-23T15:54:05.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Apps</h2><h3>Productivity</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/pdfpc/pdfpc\">pdfpc</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/pdfpc/pdfpc\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">1.3k</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":1276,\"repo\":\"pdfpc/pdfpc\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - A GTK presenter application with multi-monitor support for PDF files.</li>","updatedAt":"2022-07-23T15:54:05.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Libraries</h2><h3>Data Structures &#x26; Data Types</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://wiki.gnome.org/Projects/Libgee\">Libgee</a> - A utility library providing GObject-based interfaces and classes for commonly used data structures (lists, maps, queues, trees, etc.).</li>","updatedAt":"2022-07-23T13:55:35.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Libraries</h2><h3>Command-line</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/naaando/console-command\">console-command</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/naaando/console-command\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">1</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":1,\"repo\":\"naaando/console-command\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - Library to route command-line arguments to a Command pattern object, current implementation covers extension by inheritance or using closures.</li>","updatedAt":"2022-07-23T12:52:16.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Libraries</h2><h3>GUI Programming</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.gtk.org/\">GTK</a> - The de facto library for GUI development in Vala. Bindings are included with the vala compiler.</li>","updatedAt":"2021-06-28T22:14:39.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Libraries</h2><h3>Data Structures &#x26; Data Types</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/lcallarec/united\">United</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/lcallarec/united\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">11</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":11,\"repo\":\"lcallarec/united\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - A library for unit manipulation (like kilograms, meters, etc).</li>","updatedAt":"2020-10-06T23:10:21.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Libraries</h2><h3>Data Structures &#x26; Data Types</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/ebassi/graphene\">Graphene</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/ebassi/graphene\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">317</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":317,\"repo\":\"ebassi/graphene\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - A thin layer of types for graphic libraries. It provides common types needed to handle 3D transformations: points, triangles, rectangles, quads, quaternions, vectors, matrices, spheres, etc.</li>","updatedAt":"2018-11-30T21:20:51.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Libraries</h2><h3>Data Structures &#x26; Data Types</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/arteymix/numeric-glib\">Numeric-GLib</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/arteymix/numeric-glib\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">9</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":9,\"repo\":\"arteymix/numeric-glib\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - A collection of numeric data types for GLib (and Vala) via GCC extensions. It includes 128 bit integers &#x26; floats, complex types, vectorized operations, and decimal types.</li>","updatedAt":"2018-11-30T21:20:51.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Libraries</h2><h3>Graphics Libraries</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://cairographics.org/\">Cairo</a> - A 2D graphics library with support for multiple output devices. This is pretty much the default library you get in Vala.</li>","updatedAt":"2018-11-30T21:20:51.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Libraries</h2><h3>Graphics Libraries</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://gegl.org/\">GEGL</a> - A data flow based image processing framework, providing floating point processing and non-destructive image processing capabilities. Think of it as \"Reactive Programming for Images\".</li>","updatedAt":"2018-11-30T21:20:51.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Libraries</h2><h3>Multimedia Processing</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://gstreamer.freedesktop.org/\">GStreamer</a> - A powerful framework for creating multimedia applications.</li>","updatedAt":"2018-11-30T21:20:51.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Libraries</h2><h3>Templating</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/arteymix/compose\">Compose</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/arteymix/compose\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">16</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":16,\"repo\":\"arteymix/compose\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - A functional templating library for Vala.</li>","updatedAt":"2018-11-30T21:20:51.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Libraries</h2><h3>Templating</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://gitlab.gnome.org/GNOME/template-glib\">template-glib</a> - A library for template expansion which supports calling into GObject Introspection from templates.</li>","updatedAt":"2018-11-30T21:20:51.000Z"}]},"previous":{"id":"awesomes/github.com/koolamusic/awesome-imba","repo":"koolamusic/awesome-imba"},"next":{"id":"awesomes/github.com/coq-community/awesome-coq","repo":"coq-community/awesome-coq"}},"pageContext":{"type":"week","repo":"desiderantes/awesome-vala","id":"awesomes/github.com/desiderantes/awesome-vala","previousId":"awesomes/github.com/koolamusic/awesome-imba","nextId":"awesomes/github.com/coq-community/awesome-coq"}},"staticQueryHashes":["228695001","2744905544","2828988102"]}